\"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"enumeratum-macros_3 is a Scala 3 compile-time macro implementation normally reached through the public enumeratum_3 API, not by direct Java/runtime calls to the macro classes.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.beachape:enumeratum_3:1.9.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The documented user-facing API is com.beachape:enumeratum_3; it depends on enumeratum-macros_3 and exposes Enum/ValueEnum methods such as findValues that invoke these macros during Scala compilation.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use Scala 3 test sources that define small enumeratum Enum and, if covering ValueEnumMacros, ValueEnum examples through the public enumeratum API. For Scala 3 ValueEnum coverage, configure the Scala compiler option -Yretain-trees as documented by Enumeratum; otherwise ValueEnum macro use may fail or be incomplete. Do not try to exercise EnumMacros or ValueEnumMacros directly from Java because their public signatures require Scala quoted macro internals.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The macro implementation runs at Scala test compilation time, while native-image runtime tests may only execute the generated enum code; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether this produces useful reachability coverage.\",\n    \"The Scala 3 compiler version in the artifact POM is 3.3.5; the repository's normal Scala 3 scaffold should use a compatible compiler.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ae1dcf4ee1bef75016a3d92b702708190b283b36905dcf098\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1913, "output": 759, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34928, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782420141694, "responseI